label.value: inviable elongated mononucleate vegetative cell with mislocalized septum

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell contains a single septum, has one nucleus, is elongated, and is inviable. The septum is in an abnormal location, and the nucleus is located in one compartment of the septated cell.

definition.value: In cells with this phenotype, septation has proceeded despite chromosome segregation failing to complete normally. Chromosome segregation may be incomplete or entirely abolished. Consider also annotating to 'cut' (FYPO:0003155), 'septation following abnormal chromosome segregation, with binucleate and anucleate compartment formation' (FYPO:0003166), or their descendants, because these phenotypes often co-occur. Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

label.value: inviable swollen elongated mononucleate vegetative cell with mislocalized septum near new end

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell contains a single septum, has one nucleus, is swollen, is elongated, and is inviable. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal. The septum is in an abnormal location, and the nucleus is located in one compartment of the septated cell. The cell compartment containing the nucleus is swollen (i.e. has a larger diameter than the other compartment).

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

label.value: normal growth on polymyxin B

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing polymyxin B.

label.value: RNA absent from cell during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell is too low to detect when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0.

label.value: abnormal nucleoside diphosphate kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of nucleoside diphosphate kinase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased nucleoside diphosphate kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of nucleoside diphosphate kinase activity is decreased.

label.value: increased nucleoside diphosphate kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of nucleoside diphosphate kinase activity is increased.

label.value: inviable septated mononucleate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell is inviable, and contains one nucleus and one or more septa. The nucleus is not in the normal location.

definition.value: In cells with this phenotype, septation has proceeded despite chromosome segregation failing to complete normally. Chromosome segregation may be incomplete or entirely abolished. Consider also annotating to 'cut' (FYPO:0003155), 'septation following abnormal chromosome segregation, with binucleate and anucleate compartment formation' (FYPO:0003166), or their descendants, because these phenotypes often co-occur.

label.value: multiseptate vegetative cell, septa grouped

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell has one or more nuclei and more than one septum, and the septa are grouped together between two compartments, one or more of which may contain one or multiple nuclei.

label.value: abolished RNA polymerase II proximal promoter sequence-specific DNA binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which DNA binding at an RNA polymerase II proximal promoter by a gene product does not occur, when a gene or the bound DNA sequence is mutated. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene. An RNA polymerase II proximal promoter is a sequence of DNA that is in cis with and relatively close to a core promoter for RNA polymerase II.

label.value: microtubules absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cell does not contain detectable microtubules of one or more types.

label.value: lobate nuclear envelope

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the nuclear envelope has a lobate cross-section, i.e. one in which the edge has deep indentations or undulations that form lobes.

definition.value: This term differs from 'nuclear envelope protrusion present' (FYPO:0003788) in that a lobate envelope has a few deep fissures extending inward from the cytoplasm that appear to partially divide the nucleus into portions, whereas protrusions are smaller and extend outward from the bulk of the nucleus.

label.value: increased cellular iron level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of iron ions measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: abnormal chromosome morphology, single irregular mass

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromosomes form a single, irregularly-shaped mass in the nucleus.

label.value: decreased aconitate hydratase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of aconitate hydratase (also known as aconitase) activity is decreased.

label.value: decreased oxygen consumption during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of oxygen consumed by cells in a given time is lower than in wild type.

label.value: increased level of iron ion starvation-induced proteins

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein encoded by genes normally induced during iron ion starvation measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased level of hydrogen peroxide-induced proteins during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein encoded by genes normally induced by exposure to hydrogen peroxide measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased level of iron ion starvation-repressed proteins

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein encoded by genes normally repressed during iron ion starvation measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: normal protein oxidation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein oxidation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased RNA level during cellular response to iron ion starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to iron ion starvation is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: sensitive to iron ion starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to iron ion starvation.

label.value: sensitive to oxygen

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to oxygen. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a level of oxygen that allows wild type cells to grow.

definition.value: Also consider the term 'sensitive to oxidative stress' (FYPO:0000726).

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic interphase before NETO

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the mitotic cell cycle is arrested during G2 phase, before new end take-off (NETO) has occurred, under conditions where arrest does not normally occur.

label.value: mitotic spindle absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cell does not contain a detectable mitotic spindle.

label.value: elongated telomeres during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form telomeres that are longer than normal.

label.value: increased RNA level during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: dispersed actin cortical patch localization during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin cortical patches are localized throughout the cell cortex (rather than concentrated at the cell ends as in wild type cells).

label.value: normal actin cortical patch morphology

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, and structure of actin cortical patches are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal septum morphology during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, or structure of the septum is abnormal.

definition.value: Note that an abnormal septum organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in abnormal septum morphology.

label.value: inviable elongated multinucleate aseptate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable, is elongated, has no septum, and contains more than one nucleus.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

label.value: inviable elongated multinucleate vegetative cell with abnormal septum morphology

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable, is elongated, contains a septum with abnormal morphology (i.e. size, shape, or structure), and contain more than one nucleus.

definition.value: In cells with this phenotype, an abnormal septum forms on the surface from one side of the cell and then extends in a disorganized manner into the interior. Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

label.value: actomyosin contractile ring displaced from midpoint

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell forms an actomyosin contractile ring that is perpendicular to the long axis of the cell, but is not located at the midpoint of the long axis.

label.value: angled actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell forms an actomyosin contractile ring that is not perpendicular to the long axis of the cell.

definition.value: Note that a cell that has this phenotype will usually also subsequently display the phenotype 'binucleate monoseptate cell, with angled septum' (FYPO:0002156).

label.value: multiple actomyosin contractile rings present

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains more than one actomyosin contractile ring.

label.value: abnormal cell division, large and small daughter cells

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell divides asymmetrically, resulting in the formation of daughter cells that are not the same size.

label.value: abnormal actin cable organization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin cable organization is abnormal. The process normally results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an actin cable. Actin cables are parallel actin filament bundles nucleated by formin, and are the most common form of actin filament bundles found in yeasts.

label.value: abnormal actin cable morphology

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, or structure of actin cables is abnormal. Actin cables are parallel actin filament bundles nucleated by formin, and are the most common form of actin filament bundles found in yeasts.

label.value: abnormal actin cable morphology during mitosis

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, or structure of actin cables is abnormal during mitosis. Actin cables are parallel actin filament bundles nucleated by formin, and are the most common form of actin filament bundles found in yeasts.

label.value: abolished protein phosphorylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal DNA topoisomerase type I activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of DNA topoisomerase type I activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased DNA topoisomerase type I activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of DNA topoisomerase type I activity is decreased.

label.value: abnormal endodeoxyribonuclease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of an endodeoxyribonuclease activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased endodeoxyribonuclease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of an endodeoxyribonuclease activity is decreased.

label.value: abnormal deadenylation-independent decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which deadenylation-independent decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA is abnormal. This decapping process is cleavage of the 5'-cap of a nuclear-transcribed mRNA, independent of poly(A) tail shortening. All RNA decapping may be abnormal, or one or more specific RNA molecules may be selectively affected.

label.value: decreased deadenylation-independent decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of deadenylation-independent decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA is decreased. All RNA decapping may be decreased, or one or more specific RNA molecules may be selectively affected.

label.value: increased deadenylation-independent decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of deadenylation-independent decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA is increased. All RNA decapping may be increased, or one or more specific RNA molecules may be selectively affected.

label.value: abolished deadenylation-independent decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which deadenylation-independent decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA does not occur. All RNA decapping may be abolished, or one or more specific RNA molecules may be selectively affected.

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to iron ion starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to iron ion starvation is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal premeiotic DNA replication

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which premeiotic DNA replication is normal.
